cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image segmentation using a modified ResNet-50 and a weakly supervised learning strategy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a surrogate task for training the network and the study of different parameterizations of the normalized Lp layer suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The application of the method to detect and segment cracks on solar cells suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the organization and retrieval of information. Finally, the use of photovoltaic as a renewable energy source suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category, which deals with the study of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
